Patricia Laffan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patricia_Laffan 0 Patricia Alice Laffan (19 March 1919 – 10 March 2014) was an English stage, film, TV and radio actress, and also, after her retirement from acting, an international fashion impresario. She was five-feet-six-inches tall, with dark reddish-brown hair and green eyes. She is best known for her film roles as the Empress Poppaea in Quo Vadis (1951) and the alien Nyah in Devil Girl from Mars (1954).
